wdi2-NY.GDP.MINR.RT.ZS.def: Mineral rents are the difference between the value of production for a stock of minerals at world prices and their total costs of production. Minerals included in the calculation are tin, gold, lead, zinc, iron, copper, nickel, silver, bauxite, and phosphate.
wdi2-NY.GDP.MINR.RT.ZS.name: Mineral rents
wdi2-NY.GDP.MINR.RT.ZS.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.
